        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 2 at 1:17PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 117 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Kenedy County Wind Farms, or 17 miles east of Armstrong, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kenedy County Wind Farms.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
